{
  "texts": [
    "The idea is to learn from the difference between the wave signals measured from undamaged and damaged samples.",
    "We generated the reference wave signals as the average of the measured wave signals of all the undamaged samples in the training dataset.",
    "Then, the input becomes a normalized difference of the signals, subtracting the reference wave signals.",
    "The insignificant change in the wavefield causes difficulty in detecting small cracks.",
    "By normalizing the difference, we scale the insignificant signals measured from samples with small cracks."
  ]
}